   "execution_count": 189,
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [

    "###### We want to make a matrix with four cols and 123015 rows - features, i.e 4 training samples: img1, img2, img3, img4."

  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 193,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# we want to make a matrix with four cols and 123015 rows - features, i.e 4 training samples: img1, img2, img3, img4.\n",
    "data=np.array([fullvector1,fullvector2, fullvector3, fullvector4]) \n",
    "data = data.T"

   "source": [

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "###### While trying to get the variance -covariance matrix for the data, numpy took a lot of time, that is where Pytorch comes in, to convert numpy array into a Pytorch tensor,  use torch.as_tensor() "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 198,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#testnormal = f.normalize(tensordata, p=2, dim=2)"

  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 199,

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#sigma = np.cov(data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#sigma.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 201,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "torchtensor = torch.as_tensor(data.T)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 202,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 203,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "torch.Size([4, 123015])"
      ]

     "execution_count": 203,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"

   ],
   "source": [

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "###### Here is the effiecient implementation of PCA from Pytorch, we use this with the torch tensor."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 204,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "U,S,V = torch.pca_lowrank(torchtensor, q=None, center=True, niter=3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 114,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "tensor([[-0.6472,  0.2525, -0.5171,  0.5000],\n",
       "        [ 0.3911,  0.6967,  0.3343,  0.5000],\n",
       "        [-0.3166, -0.4887,  0.6410,  0.5000],\n",
       "        [ 0.5727, -0.4605, -0.4582,  0.5000]], dtype=torch.float64)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 114,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "U"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 205,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "tensor([[ 1.0000e+00,  5.5511e-17, -2.7756e-17, -1.3878e-16],\n",
       "        [ 5.5511e-17,  1.0000e+00,  9.7145e-17,  1.1102e-16],\n",
       "        [-2.7756e-17,  9.7145e-17,  1.0000e+00,  0.0000e+00],\n",
       "        [-1.3878e-16,  1.1102e-16,  0.0000e+00,  1.0000e+00]],\n",
       "       dtype=torch.float64)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 205,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "torch.matmul(U, U.T)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 206,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "tensor([[ 1.0000e+00,  2.1563e-16, -1.4364e-17, -4.8768e-18],\n",
       "        [ 2.1563e-16,  1.0000e+00,  3.5649e-17,  1.1247e-17],\n",
       "        [-1.4364e-17,  3.5649e-17,  1.0000e+00, -1.7117e-17],\n",
       "        [-4.8768e-18,  1.1247e-17, -1.7117e-17,  1.0000e+00]],\n",
       "       dtype=torch.float64)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 206,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "torch.matmul(V.T, V)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 207,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "tensor([3.3262e+01, 2.4947e+01, 1.8995e+01, 3.2861e-14], dtype=torch.float64)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 207,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "S"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# The relation of (U, S, V) to PCA is as follows:\n",
    "\n",
    "# A is a data matrix with m samples and n features\n",
    "\n",
    "# the V columns represent the principal directions\n",
    "\n",
    "# S ** 2 / (m - 1) contains the eigenvalues of A.T * A / (m - 1)\n",
    "# \n",
    "# which is the covariance of A when center=True is provided.\n",
    "\n",
    "# matmul(A, V[:, :k]) projects data to the first k principal components"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 115,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "torch.Size([4, 4])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 115,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "U.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 116,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "torch.Size([4])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 116,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "S.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 117,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "torch.Size([123015, 4])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 117,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "V.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 56,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Let K be 100000, lets take the first K Principle components \n",
    "\n",
    "#datareduced = torch.matmul(torchtensor)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 57,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#matmul(A, V[:, :k]) projects data to the first k principal components"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 58,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#datareduced"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 59,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#datareduced.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 60,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Let the projection be to the first 10000 components.\n",
    "# torchtensor.shape == ([4, 123015]) V.shape == torch.Size([123015, 4])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "###### We are using the K first important principal components and we can vary K, we wish to project the data into a different dimension."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 118,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "zresult=torch.matmul(torchtensor.T, V.T[:, :5000])      # here K = 5000  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 119,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "torch.Size([123015, 5000])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 119,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "zresult.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "###### We project back the PCA result to its original dimensions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 120,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "xapprox  = torch.matmul(V.T[:, :5000], zresult.T)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 121,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "torch.Size([4, 123015])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 121,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "xapprox.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 122,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
